The FIX
Totalsports TFG said that its brands will honour all lockdown regulations as stipulated by the South African government. Strict adherence to sanitisation, curfews and limited shoppers in stores throughout the Black Friday and Christmas trade will be adhered to. You can find out more about some of the deals on offer here. Mr Price <img class="aligncenter wp-image-49370" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/MR-Price-online.png" alt="MR Price online" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/MR-Price-online.png 600w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/MR-Price-online-300x200.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Mr Price said that its online Black Friday 2020 sale will run between 23 – 27 November and will offer deals on men’s, ladies’ and kids’ fashion items. This will include deals on denim, dresses, shoes, shorts, and shirts, it said. The group said it will offer in-store deals on Black Friday itself (27 November) to shop for even more deals. Mr Price said that it will also be offering online-only tech deals on Cyber Monday (3 December) . Takealot and Superbalist <img class="size-full wp-image-443850 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Takealot-Blue-Dot-Sale.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Takealot-Blue-Dot-Sale.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Takealot-Blue-Dot-Sale-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Online retailer Takealot has said it will extend its annual Blue Dot Sale to the entire month of November. In the lead-up to the Blue Dot Sale, which kicks off at one-minute past midnight on Black Friday (27 November), Takealot said it will offer three weeks of Blue Dot Countdown deals. From 2 to 26 November, Takealot.com will release thousands of new deals every week. “These Blue Dot Countdown deals won’t be beaten on Black Friday and stock is limited, meaning that shoppers need to act fast as well as return each week to take advantage of incredible new deals and savings,” the group said. Week one and two of deals have ended. Week three (16 – 22 November) will see new deals released on camping and outdoor, home improvement and power tools, as well as household essentials. Takealot said it will also give shoppers exclusive early access to some of its Black Friday deals from 23 – 26 November. Over 200 new deals will be released daily exclusively on the Takealot App, it said. Online clothing retailer Superbalist said its Black Friday deals will run over six days from 25 – 30 November. This will include deals on Adidas, Nike, Converse, Fitbit, Timberland, and Missguided, it said. Zando <img class="size-full wp-image-449051 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Zando.png" alt="" width="1715" height="854" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Zando.png 1715w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Zando-300x149.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Zando-1024x510.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Zando-768x382.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Zando-1536x765.png 1536w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Zando-1200x598.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> Online clothing retailer Zando launched its Black Friday sale on 6 November, with deals set to continue until 30 December. The online retailer said that this will include savings of up to 70% off over 800 top brands like: Adidas
